# Base Camp Awareness

> Source: Komatik/.cursor/rules/KOMATIK-BASE-CAMP-PROMPT.md
> Last distributed: 2026-04-15

## What Is Base Camp?

17 AI agents run 24/7 on a headless NUC, creating branches, opening PRs, and merging
code into `dev` continuously. **You are the last line of defense** before code reaches
`staging` or `master`.

## 4 Mandatory Workflows

### 1. Session Start
```bash
git fetch origin --prune
git log --oneline HEAD..origin/main | wc -l
gh pr list --state open --json number,title,headRefName --jq '.[] | select(.headRefName | test("^(claude/|agent/)")) | "#\(.number) — \(.title)"'
```
```
CallMcpTool(server="user-komatik-readonly", toolName="query_events", arguments={"limit": 10})
CallMcpTool(server="user-komatik-readonly", toolName="get_messages", arguments={"agent_id": "cursor-workspace"})
```

### 2. Before Any New Task
```bash
gh pr list --state all --limit 50 --json number,title,state --jq '.[] | select(.title | test("KEYWORD"; "i")) | "\(.state) #\(.number) — \(.title)"'
git branch -r | grep -i "KEYWORD"
```

### 3. Reviewing Agent PRs — 10-Point Security Checklist
A single BLOCKING failure = reject the PR.

1. **No destructive SQL** — BLOCKING
2. **RLS on new tables** — BLOCKING
3. **Auth on API routes** — BLOCKING
4. **No secrets in code** — BLOCKING
5. **No force pushes** — BLOCKING
6. **Prompt sanitization** — BLOCKING
7. **Ownership checks** — HIGH
8. **Rate limiting** — HIGH
9. **Type safety** — HIGH
10. **Import resolution** — MEDIUM

### 4. After Agent Merges — Stability Check
```bash
git checkout main && git pull origin main
npm run build
npm test
```

## Agent Branch Patterns

| Pattern | Origin |
|---------|--------|
| `claude/<two-word-slug>` | Claude Code on NUC |
| `agent/<agent-id>/<desc>` | OpenClaw scheduled agent |
| `cursor/<desc>-<4hex>` | Cursor on NUC |
| `cursor/<desc>` (no hex) | Probably YOUR workspace |

## Trust Levels

**HIGH TRUST (quick review)**: docs, dependency patches, lint fixes, tests
**VERIFY CAREFULLY**: pipeline logic, model routing, UI, API routes
**ALWAYS LINE-BY-LINE**: schema migrations, RLS, Stripe/payment, auth, Edge Functions

## MCP Bridge — Read + Write

Read tools (query state):
```
CallMcpTool(server="user-komatik-readonly", toolName="get_system_health", arguments={})
CallMcpTool(server="user-komatik-readonly", toolName="query_agent_runs", arguments={"limit": 10})
CallMcpTool(server="user-komatik-readonly", toolName="query_events", arguments={"limit": 10})
```

Write tools (coordinate with NUC agents):
```
CallMcpTool(server="user-komatik-readonly", toolName="send_message", arguments={"to_agent": "coordinator", "subject": "...", "body": "...", "priority": "normal"})
CallMcpTool(server="user-komatik-readonly", toolName="create_task", arguments={"project_slug": "undercurrent", "title": "...", "priority": "medium"})
CallMcpTool(server="user-komatik-readonly", toolName="update_task_status", arguments={"task_id": "<uuid>", "column": "done"})
```

All writes are rate-limited and tagged `cursor-workspace`. NEVER conclude Base Camp "hasn't launched" from git alone — query the bridge first.

## Emergency: Agent Merged Bad Code

1. `git revert <hash> --no-edit && git push origin main`
2. Close open PRs from the same agent session
3. Notify David with PR number and what was destructive

## The Rule

> The agents work for us. We don't work for them.
> Check before you build. Review before you merge. Test before you promote.
